## ğŸ¯ Getting Accurate Counts

### Form Requirements

For a rep to count, you must:

1. âœ… **Start extended** (elbow > 120Â°)
2. âœ… **Go down to 80Â°** (Â±30Â° tolerance)
3. âœ… **Keep arm parallel to back** (<40Â° difference)
4. âœ… **Return to extended** (elbow > 120Â°)

### Position Requirements

Counter only works when:

1. âœ… **Legs straight** (knee angle > 160Â°)
2. âœ… **Body horizontal** (plank position)
3. âœ… **Face pointing down**

### Tips for Best Results

- ğŸ”¥ **Good lighting** - helps pose detection significantly
- ğŸ“ **Full body visible** - shoulders to ankles on screen
- ğŸ¯ **Side angle** - 45-90Â° from straight-on
- âš¡ **Stable camera** - no shaking or movement
- ğŸ‘• **Fitted clothing** - helps keypoint detection

## âš™ï¸ Advanced Settings

### Adjusting Counting Sensitivity

To make counting more lenient, edit `pushup_counter.js`:

```javascript
// In PushupCounter constructor (around line 8)
this.downAngle = 80;           // Lower = need less depth
this.angleTolerance = 30;      // Higher = more forgiving
this.upThreshold = 120;        // Lower = less extension needed
this.parallelThreshold = 40;   // Higher = less strict on form
```

### Disabling Position Validation

In `pushup_counter.js`, line 235, change:

```javascript
// From:
if (this.positionValid) {
    const repCompleted = this.counter.update(elbowAvg, armBackDiff);

// To:
if (true) {  // Always allow counting
    const repCompleted = this.counter.update(elbowAvg, armBackDiff);
```

