## ğŸ“ Understanding the Metrics

### Elbow Angle
- **180Â°** = Arm completely straight (top position)
- **120Â°** = Extended, rep complete
- **80Â°** = Target bottom position
- **50Â°** = Very deep (below tolerance)

### Arm-Back Angle
- **0Â°** = Perfectly parallel (rare)
- **<20Â°** = Good form, arms close to body
- **20-40Â°** = Acceptable (shows [PARALLEL])
- **>40Â°** = Arms flaring out, not counted

### Knee Angle
- **180Â°** = Perfectly straight legs
- **160Â°** = Minimum for valid plank
- **<160Â°** = Bent knees, position invalid

